HEADWORD: Recomfort
<hw>Re*com"fort</hw> <pr>(r?*k?m"f?rt)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>re-</ets> + <ets>comfort</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧conforter</ets>.]</ety> <def>To comfort again; to console
anew; to give new strength to.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gan her <qex>recomfort</qex> from so sad affright.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recomfortless</ent>⟦br⟧
